{"title_page": "Axel Witsel", "text_new": "{{short description|Belgian footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Axel Witsel\n| image = Witsel celebrating bronze.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Witsel celebrating the bronze medal with [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]\n| fullname = Axel Laurent Angel Lambert Witsel<ref>{{cite web |url=http://portal2013.fpf.pt/DesktopModules/Bring2mind/DMX/Download.aspx?language=pt-PT&EntryId=15142&Command=Core_Download&PortalId=0&TabId=590 |title=Conselho de disciplina |trans-title=Disciplinary board |publisher=Portuguese Football Federation |format=PDF |page=3 |date=23 March 2012 |language=Portuguese |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160309014154/http://portal2013.fpf.pt/DesktopModules/Bring2mind/DMX/Download.aspx?language=pt-PT&EntryId=15142&Command=Core_Download&PortalId=0&TabId=590 |archivedate=9 March 2016}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|1|12|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_Squadlists.pdf |title=FIFA World Cup Russia 2018: List of players: Belgium |publisher=FIFA |format=PDF |page=3 |date=15 July 2018 |accessdate=11 June 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Li\u00e8ge]], Belgium\n| height = 1.86 m<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/axel-witsel_prs103426/person.shtml |title=Axel Witsel |publisher=Eurosport |accessdate=11 June 2019}}</ref>\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Borussia Dortmund]]\n| clubnumber = 28\n| youthyears1 = 1995\u20131997\n| youthclubs1 = RRC Vottem\n| youthyears2 = 1997\u20131999\n| youthclubs2 = [[CS Vis\u00e9]]\n| youthyears3 = 1999\u20132006\n| youthclubs3 = [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]]\n| years1 = 2006\u20132011\n| clubs1 = [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]]\n| caps1 = 148\n| goals1 = 33\n| years2 = 2011\u20132012\n| clubs2 = [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n| caps2 = 32\n| goals2 = 1\n| years3 = 2012\u20132016\n| clubs3 = [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]]\n| caps3 = 122\n| goals3 = 16\n| years4 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs4 = [[Tianjin Quanjian F.C.|Tianjin Quanjian]]\n| caps4 = 36\n| goals4 = 5\n| years5 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs5 = [[Borussia Dortmund]]\n| caps5 = 54\n| goals5 = 8\n| nationalyears1 = 2004\n| nationalteam1 = [[Belgium national youth football team|Belgium U15]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 1\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2005\n| nationalteam2 = [[Belgium national youth football team|Belgium U16]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 2\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2005\u20132006\n| nationalteam3 = [[Belgium national under-17 football team|Belgium U17]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 19\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2006\u20132007\n| nationalteam4 = [[Belgium national under-18 football team|Belgium U18]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 5\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| nationalyears5 = 2006\n| nationalteam5 = [[Belgium national under-19 football team|Belgium U19]]\n| nationalcaps5 = 3\n| nationalgoals5 = 0\n| nationalyears6 = 2007\u20132009\n| nationalteam6 = [[Belgium national under-21 football team|Belgium U21]]\n| nationalcaps6 = 10\n| nationalgoals6 = 0\n| nationalyears7 = 2008\u2013\n| nationalteam7 = [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]]\n| nationalcaps7 = 105\n| nationalgoals7 = 9\n| medaltemplates = {{Medal|Sport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{Medal|Country|{{fb|BEL}}}}\n{{Medal|Comp|[[FIFA World Cup]]}}\n{{Medal|3rd|[[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 Russia]]|}}\n| club-update = 23:14, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 19:36, 16 November 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Axel Laurent Angel Lambert Witsel''' (born 12 January 1989) is a Belgian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for German club [[Borussia Dortmund]].<ref name=\"Borussia\">{{cite web|publisher=[[Borussia Dortmund]]|url=https://www.bvb.de/News/Uebersicht/Axel-Witsel-im-BVB-Trainingslager-angekommen|title=Axel Witsel im BVB Trainingslager angekommen|date=6 August 2017|language=German}}</ref> During his play for the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]], he came into the first team as a [[Midfielder#Winger|right-winger]], and can also play [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]], though his natural position is as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]].\n\nHe began his career at hometown club [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]], making 183 appearances and scoring 42 goals while winning five domestic trophies. He was awarded the [[Belgian Golden Shoe]] in 2008. After a season in Portugal with [[S.L. Benfica]], he signed for [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] for a \u20ac40 million fee in 2012. Witsel won four honours during his time in Russia, before leaving for [[Tianjin Quanjian F.C.|Tianjin Quanjian]] in January 2017. He returned to Europe with Borussia Dortmund in August 2018.\n\nWitsel made his senior international debut in 2008 and  earned his 100th [[cap (sport)|cap]] for Belgium on 15 November 2018. He represented the country at the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]], [[UEFA Euro 2016]] and the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], helping them to third place in the last tournament.\n\n==Club career==\n===Standard Li\u00e8ge===\nOn 17 September 2006, a 17-year-old Witsel made his debut with [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]] during a competitive game against [[FC Brussels]] when he replaced [[Steven Defour]] in the 89th minute. Eleven days later, he made his European debut as a [[substitute (football)|substitute]].\n\n\nDuring the [[2007\u201308 Belgian First Division|2007\u201308]] season, at 18 years of age, he was a key member in the squad of Standard Li\u00e8ge, winners of the Belgian League title that year. During this year, he formed a very young midfield together with other Belgian talents Defour and [[Marouane Fellaini]]. In the [[2008\u201309 Belgian First Division|following season]], he scored the winning goal [[Penalty kick (association football)|from the penalty spot]] in a [[two-legged match|two-legged playoff]] to decide the championship.\n\nOn 30 August 2009, Witsel sparked controversy when he broke [[Marcin Wasilewski]]'s leg by stamping on his ankle during the match between [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] and Standard.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Sporza |title=Witsel breekt been van Wasilewski in tackle |url=http://www.sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/Jupiler_Pro_League/090830_Wasilewski_tackle_Witsel |accessdate=31 August 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090901061702/http://www.sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/Jupiler_Pro_League/090830_Wasilewski_tackle_Witsel |archivedate=1 September 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=YouTube|title=Anderlecht-Standard faute d'Axel Witsel sur Wasilewski |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_OapMvlhZOQ|accessdate=31 August 2009}}</ref> Following the tackle, Witsel protested the red card, claiming that it was an accident without intent, before being sent off the pitch. He soon apologised, but was the subject of criticism from several media outlets and numerous [[death threat]]s from angry Anderlecht and [[Poland national football team|Poland]] fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goal.com/en/news/755/europe/2009/09/01/1474358/standard-liege-stars-defour-witsel-receive-death-threats|title=Standard Liege Stars Defour & Witsel Receive Death Threats - Report - Goal.com|date=1 September 2009|publisher=|accessdate=26 June 2016}}</ref> The initial ban until 23 November by the [[Royal Belgian Football Association|Belgian Football Association]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/standard-liege-midfielder-axel-witsel-3372233|title=Standard Liege midfielder Axel Witsel banned for horror tackle|work=MirrorFootball|date=1 September 2009|publisher=|accessdate=26 June 2016}}</ref> was later reduced on appeal to eight matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/05092009/58/champions-league-witsel-horror-tackle-ban-reduced.html|title=Yahoo UK & Ireland \u2013 Sports News \u2013 Live Scores \u2013 Results|publisher=|accessdate=26 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Benfica===\nWitsel signed for Portuguese club [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] on a five-year deal on 13 July 2011, including a \u20ac40 million buyout clause.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/news/story/_/id/934507/benfica-complete-signing-of-belgium-international-axel-witsel?cc=5901 |title=Benfica sign Witsel |publisher=ESPNFC |date=14 July 2011}}</ref> Witsel scored twice in the 3\u20131 win against [[FC Twente]], in the [[2011\u201312 UEFA Champions League|Champions League play-off second leg]], on 24 August 2011, sending Benfica to the group stages with a 5\u20133 aggregate victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2012/matches/round=2000262/match=2007565/postmatch/report/index.html |title=Witsel delivers as Benfica oust Twente |publisher=UEFA |date=24 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Axel Witsel.jpg|thumb|left|Witsel playing for [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] against Zenit in 2012]]\nHe scored the opening goal in a 4\u20131 thrashing of [[Vit\u00f3ria S.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Guimar\u00e3es]] in the [[2011\u201312 Ta\u00e7a da Liga|Ta\u00e7a da Liga]] on 9 January 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lpfp.pt/taca_liga/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20112012&jornada=6&jogo=7308 |title=V.Guimar\u00e3es 1\u20134 Benfica |publisher=LPFP |accessdate=3 December 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120428112211/http://www.lpfp.pt/taca_liga/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20112012&jornada=6&jogo=7308 |archive-date=28 April 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He then assisted [[Nolito]] in a 4\u20131 league defeat of [[Vit\u00f3ria F.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Set\u00fabal]]. Witsel scored his fourth goal against [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]] on 18 January in a Ta\u00e7a da Liga match.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lpfp.pt/taca_liga/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20112012&jornada=7&jogo=7310 |title=Benfica 2\u20130 Sta. Clara |publisher=LPFP |accessdate=3 December 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130801085810/http://www.lpfp.pt/taca_liga/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20112012&jornada=7&jogo=7310 |archive-date=1 August 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Benfica reached the final on 14 April against [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]] and Witsel was awarded the [[Man of the Match]] award as Benfica claimed their fourth Ta\u00e7a da Liga title with a 2\u20131 victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lpfp.pt/Pages/WitselfoioManofTheMatch.aspx |title=Witsel foi o Man of The Match |publisher=LPFP |date=15 April 2012 |access-date=3 December 2012 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120714053927/http://lpfp.pt/Pages/WitselfoioManofTheMatch.aspx |archive-date=14 July 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===Zenit Saint Petersburg===\nOn 3 September 2012, Witsel signed for [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] for \u20ac40 million, after signing a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fc-zenit.ru/main/news/60736.html|title=\u041e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u0430\u0439\u0442 \u0424\u041a \"\u0417\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\"|publisher=|accessdate=26 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://web3.cmvm.pt/sdi2004/emitentes/docs/FR41312.pdf |title=Comunicado |language=Portuguese |trans-title=Announcement |date=3 September 2012 |publisher=[[Portuguese Securities Market Commission|CMVM]] |format=PDF |accessdate=31 December 2014}}</ref> Witsel made his debut in the [[2012\u201313 Russian Premier League|Russian Premier League]] on 14 September, replacing [[Konstantin Zyryanov]] in the 70th minute as Zenit fell 2\u20130 to [[FC Terek Grozny|Terek Grozny]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/match?id=342396&cc=5901 |title=Zenit 0 \u2013 2 Terek Grozny |publisher=ESPNFC |date=14 September 2012}}</ref> He scored his first two goals for the club on 30 November when Zenit brushed aside [[FC Spartak Moscow|Spartak Moscow]] 4\u20132 at the [[Luzhniki Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espnfc.com/us/en/gamecast/statistics/id/357869/statistics.html?soccernet=true&cc=5901 |title=Spartak Moscow 2 \u2013 4 Zenit St Petersburg |publisher=ESPNFC |date=30 November 2012}}</ref> Witsel scored Zenit's winner against Terek Grozny on 30 March 2013, an eighth-minute strike, as his side cruised to a 3\u20130 league victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espnfc.com/us/en/gamecast/statistics/id/358127/statistics.html?soccernet=true&cc=5901 |title=Terek Grozny 0\u20133 Zenit St. Petersburg |publisher=ESPNFC |date=30 March 2013 }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Axel Witsel 2014.jpg|thumb|right|Witsel playing for [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] in 2014]]\nIn Zenit's first match of the [[2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group C|2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League group stage]] on 16 September 2014, Witsel scored Zenit's second goal in a 2\u20130 away victory over former club Benfica.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/news/newsid=2140402.html |title=Familiar Zenit faces come back to haunt Benfica |work=UEFA |date=16 September 2014 |accessdate=17 July 2015 }}</ref> After finishing third in their Champions League group, Zenit were parachuted into the [[2014-15 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] knockout phase; in the first leg of their Round of 16 clash against [[Torino F.C.|Torino]] on 12 March 2015, Witsel scored on a rebound as Zenit defeated the Italian club 2\u20130.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2015/matches/round=2000589/match=2014609/postmatch/report/index.html#zenit+beat+torino |title=Zenit ease to victory over ten-man Torino |work=UEFA |date=12 March 2015 |accessdate=17 July 2015 }}</ref> On 26 April, Witsel scored the game's only goal in the seventeenth minute as Zenit defeated [[FC Arsenal Tula|Arsenal Tula]] in a league match at the [[Petrovsky Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/football/russian-premier-league/zenit-st-petersburg-fc-arsenal-tula-18571/ |title=Zenit St Petersburg 1\u20130 FC Arsenal Tula |work=Yahoo Sports! |date=26 April 2015 |accessdate=17 July 2015 }}</ref> On Sunday 17 May, Witsel played the full 90 minutes as Zenit drew 1\u20131 with [[FC Ufa]], earning the point they needed to secure the [[2014\u201315 Russian Premier League|Premier League]] crown, the club's fourth overall and Witsel's first with Zenit.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-3085421/Andre-Villas-Boas-leads-Zenit-St-Petersburg-Russian-Premier-League-title-ill-fated-spells-Chelsea-Tottenham.html |title=Andre Villas-Boas leads Zenit St Petersburg to Russian Premier League title after ill-fated spells at Chelsea and Tottenham |work=Daily Mail |date=17 May 2015 |accessdate=17 July 2015 }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Dundolk-Zenit (21).jpg|thumb|left|Witsel playing for [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] against Dundalk in 2016]]\nIn the [[2015 Russian Super Cup]] on 12 July 2015, Witsel converted his penalty shot in a 4\u20132 penalty shoot-out victory over [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow]] after the match had finished 1\u20131.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rfpl.org/match/match_10880.html |title=\u0421\u0443\u043f\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0443\u0431\u043e\u043a \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u0444\u0443\u0442\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0443 2015, \u0424\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043b |work=RFPL |date=12 July 2015 |accessdate=17 July 2015 |language=Russian }}</ref>\n\n===Tianjin Quanjian===\nOn 3 January 2017, Zenit officially announced that Witsel has moved to Chinese club [[Tianjin Quanjian F.C.|Tianjin Quanjian]].<ref name=\"toChina\">{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg]]|url=http://fc-zenit.ru/news/feed/2017/01/03/aksel-vitsel-prodolzhit-kareru-v-kitae/|title=Witsel will continue his career in China|date=3 January 2017|language=Russian}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 March 2017, Witsel made his debut for Quanjian in a 2\u20130 loss to [[Guangzhou R&F F.C.|Guangzhou R&F]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.espnfc.com.au/chinese-super-league/story/3074387/alexandre-pato-struggles-as-tianjin-quanjian-slump-vs-guangzhou-randf|title=Alexandre Pato struggles as Tianjin Quanjian slump vs. Guangzhou R&F|date=4 March 2017|work=ESPN}}</ref> A week later he scored the club's first ever goal in the [[Chinese Super League]] during a 1\u20131 draw with [[Shanghai Greenland Shenhua F.C.|Shanghai Greenland Shenhua]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.msn.com/en-my/video/news/witsel-scores-quanjians-maiden-csl-goal/vp-AAo96zl|title=Witsel scores Quanjian's maiden CSL goal|date=11 March 2017|work=MSN}}</ref>\n\n===Borussia Dortmund===\nOn 6 August 2018, Witsel signed for [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia Dortmund]] and agreed a four-year contract which lasts until 30 June 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11899/11463405/axel-witsel-to-join-borussia-dortmund-from-tianjin-quanjian|title=Axel Witsel to join Borussia Dortmund from Tianjin Quanjian|publisher=SkySports|accessdate=7 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bvb.de/eng/News/Overview/Axel-Witsel-arrives-at-the-BVB-training-camp|title=Axel Witsel arrives at the BVB training camp |publisher= Borussia Dortmund|accessdate=7 August 2018}}</ref> On 21 August, he scored an equalizing goal in the [[Association football#Duration and tie-breaking methods|stoppage time]] to make it 1\u20131 after coming on as a substitute on his debut for the club against [[SpVgg Greuther F\u00fcrth]] in the [[2018\u201319 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]] first round match and later his side went on to win the match in the [[Overtime (sports)|extra time]] with a 2-1 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45254350|title=Axel Witsel saves Borussia Dortmund on debut in German Cup|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=21 August 2018}}</ref> Witsel scored his first Bundesliga goal on his league debut for the club with an overhead kick in a 4\u20131 victory over [[RB Leipzig]] on 26 August.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/borussia-dortmung-rb-leipzig-live-blog-pulisic-reus-witsel-werner-delaney-511044.jsp|title=Borussia Dortmund 4-1 RB Leipzig: As it happened!|publisher=Bundesliga|accessdate=27 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nPrior to making his international debut for the senior side, he played for the [[Belgium national under-21 football team|under-21 side]] in 2007 earning nine caps as well as helping his side reach the semi-finals of the [[2007 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship]].\n\nOn 26 March 2008, Witsel made his international debut during a friendly game against [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]]. The match resulted in a 1\u20134 loss, but Witsel scored his first goal for [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]].<ref name = \"First int'l goal\">{{cite news |title=Axel Witsel marque, Stijn Stijnen se troue deux fois |url=http://archives.lesoir.be/-p-axel-witsel-marque-stijn-stijnen-se-troue-deux-fois-_t-20080327-00FFGG.html |work=Le Soir |date=27 March 2008 |accessdate=4 December 2014 |language=French}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Axel Witsel Belgium.jpg|thumb|left|Witsel lining up for [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] before playing [[Austria national football team|Austria]] in the qualification for [[UEFA Euro 2012]]]]\nWitsel's first goal in an competitive international match came a day short of three years after the Morocco goal, in the sixth minute against [[Austria national football team|Austria]] in [[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying Group A|Group A]] of the [[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying]] process, and his second would come in the second half.<ref name=\"Goals vs Austria\" /> However, Belgian hopes of qualifying for [[UEFA Euro 2012]] were dashed on 11 October 2011, by defeat to [[Germany national football team|Germany]] coupled with [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]]'s victory over [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Germany stamp out Belgium's fire|date=11 October 2011|first=Steffen|last=Potter|work=uefa.com|publisher=Union of European Football Associations|accessdate=24 January 2018|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2012/matches/round=15171/match=2002112/postmatch/report/index.html#germany+oust+belgium}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 May 2014, Witsel was named in [[2014 FIFA World Cup squads#Belgium|Belgium's squad]] for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Adnan Januzaj included in Belgium's World Cup squad|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27395150|accessdate=15 May 2014|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=13 May 2014}}</ref> He started in midfield in the team's first game of the tournament, a 2\u20131 win against [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] in [[Belo Horizonte]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chowdhury|first1=Saj|title=Belgium 2\u20131 Algeria|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/25285127|accessdate=17 June 2014|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=17 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nWitsel also featured in the [[UEFA Euro 2016 squads#Belgium|Belgian squad]] at [[UEFA Euro 2016]], announced on 31 May 2016.<ref>{{Cite tweet |author=BelgianRedDevils |user=@BelRedDevils |number=737693491627720705 |date=31 May 2016 |title=.OFFICIAL ! Our final #Euro2016 squad list & numbers ! #TousenFrance |access-date=24 January 2018}}</ref> He scored his first tournament goal during the Championships, in a [[UEFA Euro 2016 Group E|Group E]] match against the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref name = \"Euro 2016 goal\">{{cite news |first=Sid |last=Lowe |title=Belgium get going as Romelu Lukaku punishes Republic of Ireland |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2016/jun/18/belgium-republic-of-ireland-euro-2016-match-report |website=The Guardian |date=18 June 2016 |accessdate=14 October 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Axel Witsel 2018.jpg|thumb|right|Axel Witsel playing for [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] during the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]]]\nHe scored twice in [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]], both in wide victories over [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dorman |first1=Matt |title=Belgium 9 Gibraltar 0: Trebles for Meunier and Lukaku as Hazard makes scoring return |url=http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/55/main/2017/08/31/38240092/belgium-9-gibraltar-0-trebles-for-meunier-and-lukaku-as |accessdate=4 September 2018 |publisher=Goal.com |date=31 August 2017}}</ref> Manager [[Roberto Mart\u00ednez]] named him in the squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|final tournament]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite news |title=World Cup 2018: Belgium include Vincent Kompany but Christian Benteke misses out |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44353673 |accessdate=4 September 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=4 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn June 2015, Witsel married his longtime [[Romania]]n girlfriend, Rafaella, with whom he has two children.<ref>{{cite news|last1=|first1=|title=Axel Witsel en tr\u00e8s charmante compagnie|url=http://www.dhnet.be/archive/axel-witsel-en-tres-charmante-compagnie-51b7e153e4b0de6db992d370|5=|language=French|accessdate=23 April 2014|work=[[La Derni\u00e8re Heure]]|date=23 October 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170831220526/http://www.dhnet.be/archive/axel-witsel-en-tres-charmante-compagnie-51b7e153e4b0de6db992d370|archive-date=31 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sudinfo.be/1310603/article/2015-06-14/axel-rafaella-witsel-eblouissants-lors-de-leur-mariage-religieux-photos|language=French|title=Axel & Rafaella Witsel \u00e9blouissants lors de leur mariage religieux|date=13 June 2015|work=Sudinfo.be|access-date=31 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160625022110/http://www.sudinfo.be/1310603/article/2015-06-14/axel-rafaella-witsel-eblouissants-lors-de-leur-mariage-religieux-photos|archive-date=25 June 2016|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\nHe is of [[Martinique|Martiniquais]] descent through his father.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mondial 2018 - France Belgique: Axel Witsel, l'autre Antillais endiabl\u00e9 |url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mondial-2018-france-belgique-axel-witsel-autre-martiniquais-endiable-607799.html |accessdate=11 July 2018 |agency=franceinfo |publisher=franceinfo |date=10 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Dalmat |first1=Syanie |title=Axel Witsel, le Belge qui aurait pu jouer pour la France |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/Axel-witsel-un-martiniquais-chez-les-belges/920984 |accessdate=11 July 2018 |publisher=L'Equipe |date=10 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n[[File:Dundolk-Zenit (9).jpg|thumb|upright|Witsel in [[UEFA Europa League]] action for Zenit, facing [[Dundalk F.C.|Dundalk]] in 2016]]\n\n{{updated|match played 11 March 2020}}<ref name=\"honours\" />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[Standard Li\u00e8ge]]\n|[[2006\u201307 Standard Li\u00e8ge season|2006\u201307]]\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Belgian Pro League]]\n|16||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||17||2\n|-\n|[[2007\u201308 Standard Li\u00e8ge season|2007\u201308]]\n|33||7||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||3||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||36||8\n|-\n|[[2008\u201309 Standard Li\u00e8ge season|2008\u201309]]\n|35||8||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||10||1||1||0||46||9\n|-\n|[[2009\u201310 Standard Li\u00e8ge season|2009\u201310]]\n|27||6||1||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||12||3||1||1||41||11\n|-\n|[[2010\u201311 Standard Li\u00e8ge season|2010\u201311]]\n|37||10||6||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||43||12\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!148!!33!!7!!3!!0!!0!!26!!5!!2!!1!!183!!42\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n|[[2011\u201312 S.L. Benfica season|2011\u201312]]\n|rowspan=2|[[Primeira Liga]]\n|29||1||1||0||4||2||14||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||49||5\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 S.L. Benfica season|2012\u201313]]\n|3||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||3||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!32!!1!!1!!0!!4!!2!!14!!2!!0!!0!!52!!5\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]]\n|[[2012\u201313 FC Zenit Saint Petersburg season|2012\u201313]]\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Russian Football Premier League|Russian Premier League]]\n|19||4||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||9||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||31||5\n|-\n|[[2013\u201314 FC Zenit Saint Petersburg season|2013\u201314]]\n|30|||4||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||11||0||1||0||43||4\n|-\n|[[2014\u201315 FC Zenit Saint Petersburg season|2014\u201315]]\n|28||4|||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||13||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||42||6\n|-\n|[[2015\u201316 FC Zenit Saint Petersburg season|2015\u201316]]\n|29||3||4||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||7||1||1||0||41||6\n|-\n|[[2016\u201317 FC Zenit Saint Petersburg season|2016\u201317]]\n|16||1||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||6||0||0||0||23||1\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!122!!16!!10!!2!!0!!0!!46!!4!!2!!0!!180!!22\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Tianjin Quanjian F.C.|Tianjin Quanjian]]\n|[[2017 Chinese Super League|2017]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Chinese Super League]]\n|27||4||2||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||29||4\n|-\n|[[2018 Chinese Super League|2018]]\n|9||1||1||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||8||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||18||2\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!36!!5!!3!!1!!colspan=\"2\"|\u2014!!8!!0!!0!!0!!47!!6\n|-\n|rowspan=\"3\"|[[Borussia Dortmund]]\n|[[2018\u201319 Borussia Dortmund season|2018\u201319]]\n|rowspan=\"2\"|[[Bundesliga]]\n|33||4||3||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||7||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||43||6\n|-\n|[[2019\u201320 Borussia Dortmund season|2019\u201320]]\n|21||4||3||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||7||0||1||0||32||4\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!54!!8!!6!!1!!colspan=\"2\"|\u2014!!14!!1!!1!!0!!75!!10\n|-\n!colspan=\"3\"|Career total\n!392!!63!!27!!7!!4!!2!!108!!12!!5!!1!!536!!85\n|}\n[[File:2017 RUS v BEL exhibition - Axel Witsel.jpg|thumb|upright|Witsel warming up on international duty, 2017]]\n{{notelist}}\n\n===International===\n{{updated|16 November 2019}}<ref name=\"Belgium profile\"/>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!Year!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|2008||7||1\n|-\n|2009||3||1\n|-\n|2010||5||0\n|-\n|2011||11||3\n|-\n|2012||9||0\n|-\n|2013||10||0\n|-\n|2014||11||1\n|-\n|2015||9||0\n|-\n|2016||15||2\n|-\n|2017||7||1\n|-\n|2018||13||0\n|-\n|2019||5||0\n|-\n!Total||105||9\n|}\n\n===International goals===\n:''As of match played 31 August 2017. Belgium score listed first, score column indicates score after each Witsel goal.''<ref name=\"Belgium profile\">{{cite web |url=http://static.belgianfootball.be/project/publiek/jrinteren/speler_PH_5254.htm#itop |title=Axel Witsel |website=Royal Belgian Football Association |accessdate=14 October 2016}}</ref>\n\n{| class=\"wikitable sortable plainrowheaders\"\n|+ International goals by date, venue, cap, opponent, score, result and competition\n|-\n!scope=col|No.\n!scope=col data-sort-type=date|Date\n!scope=col|Venue\n!scope=col|Cap\n!scope=col|Opponent\n!scope=col|Score\n!scope=col|Result\n!scope=col|Competition\n!scope=col class=unsortable|Ref\n|-\n!scope=row|1\n|26 March 2008||[[King Baudouin Stadium]], [[Brussels]], Belgium||align=center|1||{{fb|MAR}}||align=center|'''1'''\u20132||align=center|1\u20134||rowspan=3|[[Exhibition game#Association football|Friendly]]||<ref name=\"First int'l goal\" />\n|-\n!scope=row|2\n|17 November 2009||[[Stade Louis Dugauguez]], [[Sedan, Ardennes|Sedan]], France||align=center|10||{{fb|QAT}}||align=center|'''1'''\u20130||align=center|2\u20130||<ref>{{cite news |title=Victoire des Diables face au Qatar (0\u20132) |url=http://www.dhnet.be/sports/football/diablesrouges/victoire-des-diables-face-au-qatar-0-2-51b7a60fe4b0de6db985c1fd |work=La Derni\u00e8re Heure |date=17 November 2009 |accessdate=4 December 2014 |language=French}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|3\n|9 February 2011||[[Jules Ottenstadion]], [[Ghent]], Belgium||align=center|16||{{fb|FIN}}||align=center|'''1'''\u20130||align=center|1\u20131||<ref>{{cite news |first=Christophe |last=Da Silva |title=Rode Duivels gooien verdiende winst weer weg in blessuretijd |url=http://www.hln.be/hln/nl/949/Belgisch-Voetbal/article/detail/1220329/2011/02/09/Rode-Duivels-gooien-verdiende-winst-weer-weg-in-blessuretijd.dhtml |work=Het Laatste Nieuws |date=9 February 2011 |accessdate=4 December 2014 |language=Dutch}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|4\n|rowspan=2|25 March 2011||rowspan=2|[[Ernst-Happel-Stadion]], [[Vienna]], Austria||rowspan=2 align=center|17||rowspan=2|{{fb|AUT}}||align=center|'''1'''\u20130||align=center|2\u20130||rowspan=2|[[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying Group A|UEFA Euro 2012 qualification]]||rowspan=2|<ref name = \"Goals vs Austria\">{{cite news |title=Witsel bezorgt Rode Duivels zege van de hoop |url=http://sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/Rode_Duivels/1.989145 |work=Sporza |date=25 March 2011 |accessdate=4 December 2014 |language=Dutch}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|5\n|align=center|'''2'''\u20130||align=center|2\u20130\n|-\n!scope=row|6\n|4 September 2014||[[Stade Maurice Dufrasne]], [[Li\u00e8ge]], Belgium||align=center|52||{{fb|AUS}}||align=center|'''2'''\u20130||align=center|2\u20130||Friendly||<ref>{{cite news |first=Michael |last=Lynch |title=Socceroos easily beaten by Belgium in friendly |url=https://www.smh.com.au/sport/soccer/socceroos-easily-beaten-by-belgium-in-friendly-20140904-10cqco.html |work=The Sydney Morning Herald |date=5 September 2014 |accessdate=4 December 2014}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|7\n|18 June 2016||[[Nouveau Stade de Bordeaux]], [[Bordeaux]], France||align=center|69||{{fb|IRL}}||align=center|'''2'''\u20130||align=center|3\u20130||[[UEFA Euro 2016 Group E|UEFA Euro 2016]]||<ref name=\"Euro 2016 goal\" />\n|-\n!scope=row|8\n|10 October 2016||[[Est\u00e1dio Algarve]], [[Faro, Portugal|Faro]]/[[Loul\u00e9]], Portugal||align=center|76||rowspan=2|{{fb|GIB}}||align=center|'''2'''\u20130||align=center|6\u20130||rowspan=2|[[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification \u2013 UEFA Group H|2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]]||rowspan=2|<ref>{{cite news |title=Christian Benteke historic goal, hat trick help Belgium beat Gibraltar |url=http://www.espnfc.com/report?gameId=457281 |website=ESPN FC |publisher=Entertainment and Sports Programming Network |date=10 October 2016 |accessdate=14 October 2016}}</ref>\n|-\n!scope=row|9\n|31 August 2017||[[Stade Maurice Dufrasne]], [[Li\u00e8ge]], Belgium||align=center|81||align=center|'''3'''\u20130||align=center|9\u20130\n|}\n\n==Honours==\n===Club===\n[[File:Zenit celebrating (7).jpg|thumb|right|Witsel kissing the [[Russian Premier League]] trophy, 2015]]\n\n'''Standard Li\u00e8ge'''<ref name=\"honours\">{{cite web|url=https://int.soccerway.com/players/axel-witzel/13531/|title=A. Witsel|accessdate=17 March 2015|publisher=Soccerway}}</ref>\n* [[Belgian Pro League]]: [[2007\u201308 Belgian First Division|2007\u201308]], [[2008\u201309 Belgian First Division|2008\u201309]]\n* [[Belgian Cup]]: [[2010\u201311 Belgian Cup|2010\u201311]]\n* [[Belgian Supercup]]: [[2008 Belgian Super Cup|2008]], [[2009 Belgian Super Cup|2009]]\n\n'''Benfica'''\n* [[Ta\u00e7a da Liga]]: [[2011\u201312 Ta\u00e7a da Liga|2011\u201312]]<ref name=\"honours\"/>\n\n'''Zenit'''\n* [[Russian Football Premier League]]: [[2014\u201315 Russian Premier League|2014\u201315]]\n* [[Russian Cup (football)|Russian Cup]]: [[2015\u201316 Russian Cup|2015\u201316]]\n* [[Russian Super Cup]]: [[2015 Russian Super Cup|2015]]<ref name=\"honours\"/>\n\n'''Borussia Dortmund'''\n* [[DFL-Supercup]]: [[2019 DFL-Supercup|2019]]<ref name=\"MOTM\">{{cite news |location=[[Dortmund]] |url=https://www.bundesliga.com/de/bundesliga/news/supercup-borussia-dortmund-fc-bayern-munchen-spielbericht-5996 |title=Borussia Dortmund gewinnt den Supercup 2019 gegen den FC Bayern M\u00fcnchen |trans-title=Borussia Dortmund wins the 2019 Supercup against FC Bayern Munich |website=Bundesliga.com |publisher=[[Deutsche Fu\u00dfball Liga]] |date=3 August 2019 |access-date=3 August 2019 |language=German |url-status=live |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20190803221924/https://www.bundesliga.com/de/bundesliga/news/supercup-borussia-dortmund-fc-bayern-munchen-spielbericht-5996 |archive-date=3 August 2019}}</ref>\n\n===International===\n'''Belgium'''\n*[[FIFA World Cup]] third place: [[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018]]<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_Squadlists.pdf |title=FIFA World Cup Russia 2018: List of players: Belgium |publisher=FIFA |format=PDF |page=3 |date=15 July 2018 |accessdate=11 June 2019}}</ref>\n\n===Individual===\n* [[Belgian professional football awards|Belgian Young Footballer of the Year]]: [[2007\u201308 Belgian First Division|2007\u201308]]\n* [[Belgian Golden Shoe]]: 2008<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.uefa.com/memberassociations/news/newsid=794257.html|title=Witsel honoured as Belgium's best of 2008|publisher=UEFA|date=22 January 2009|accessdate=4 August 2019}}</ref>\n* [[O Jogo|O Jogo Team of the Year]]: 2012\n\n==See also==\n{{Portal|Association football|Belgium}}\n*[[List of men's footballers with 100 or more international caps]]\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commons category}}\n*{{Official website}}\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20140804204529/http://en.fc-zenit.ru/main/team/players/14186.html Zenit profile]\n*{{ForaDeJogo}}\n*{{soccerway}}\n*{{NFT player}}\n\n{{Borussia Dortmund squad}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Belgium squads\n| bg = #E20E0E\n| fg = #FFCE4A\n| bordercolor = black\n| list1 = \n{{Belgium squad 2014 FIFA World Cup}}\n{{Belgium squad UEFA Euro 2016}}\n{{Belgium squad 2018 FIFA World Cup}}\n}}\n{{Navboxes\n| title = Awards\n| bg = gold\n| fg = navy\n| list1 = \n{{Belgian Young Professional Footballer of the Year}}\n{{Belgian Golden Shoe}}\n}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Witsel, Axel}}\n[[Category:1989 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Belgian people of French descent]]\n[[Category:Belgian people of Martiniquais descent]]\n[[Category:Sportspeople from Li\u00e8ge]]\n[[Category:Black Belgian sportspeople]]\n[[Category:Belgian footballers]]\n[[Category:Association football midfielders]]\n[[Category:Standard Li\u00e8ge players]]\n[[Category:S.L. Benfica footballers]]\n[[Category:FC Zenit Saint Petersburg players]]\n[[Category:Tianjin Tianhai F.C. players]]\n[[Category:Borussia Dortmund players]]\n[[Category:Belgian First Division A players]]\n[[Category:Primeira Liga players]]\n[[Category:Russian Premier League players]]\n[[Category:Chinese Super League players]]\n[[Category:Bundesliga players]]\n[[Category:Belgium youth international footballers]]\n[[Category:Belgium under-21 international footballers]]\n[[Category:Belgium international footballers]]\n[[Category:2014 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:UEFA Euro 2016 players]]\n[[Category:2018 FIFA World Cup players]]\n[[Category:FIFA Century Club]]\n[[Category:Belgian expatriate footballers]]\n[[Category:Belgian expatriate sportspeople in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Belgian expatriate sportspeople in Russia]]\n[[Category:Belgian expatriate sportspeople in China]]\n[[Category:Belgian expatriate sportspeople in Germany]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Portugal]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Russia]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in China]]\n[[Category:Expatriate footballers in Germany]]\n", "text_old": "{{short description|Belgian footballer}}\n{{Use dmy dates|date=July 2016}}\n{{Infobox football biography\n| name = Axel Witsel\n| image = Witsel celebrating bronze.jpg\n| image_size = \n| caption = Witsel celebrating the bronze medal with [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] at the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]\n| fullname = Axel Laurent Angel Lambert Witsel<ref>{{cite web |url=http://portal2013.fpf.pt/DesktopModules/Bring2mind/DMX/Download.aspx?language=pt-PT&EntryId=15142&Command=Core_Download&PortalId=0&TabId=590 |title=Conselho de disciplina |trans-title=Disciplinary board |publisher=Portuguese Football Federation |format=PDF |page=3 |date=23 March 2012 |language=Portuguese |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160309014154/http://portal2013.fpf.pt/DesktopModules/Bring2mind/DMX/Download.aspx?language=pt-PT&EntryId=15142&Command=Core_Download&PortalId=0&TabId=590 |archivedate=9 March 2016}}</ref>\n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1989|1|12|df=y}}<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.fifadata.com/documents/FWC/2018/pdf/FWC_2018_Squadlists.pdf |title=FIFA World Cup Russia 2018: List of players: Belgium |publisher=FIFA |format=PDF |page=3 |date=15 July 2018 |accessdate=11 June 2019}}</ref>\n| birth_place = [[Li\u00e8ge]], Belgium\n| height = 1.86 m<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.eurosport.com/football/axel-witsel_prs103426/person.shtml |title=Axel Witsel |publisher=Eurosport |accessdate=11 June 2019}}</ref>\n| position = [[Midfielder]]\n| currentclub = [[Borussia Dortmund]]\n| clubnumber = 28\n| youthyears1 = 1995\u20131997\n| youthclubs1 = RRC Vottem\n| youthyears2 = 1997\u20131999\n| youthclubs2 = [[CS Vis\u00e9]]\n| youthyears3 = 1999\u20132006\n| youthclubs3 = [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]]\n| years1 = 2006\u20132011\n| clubs1 = [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]]\n| caps1 = 148\n| goals1 = 33\n| years2 = 2011\u20132012\n| clubs2 = [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n| caps2 = 32\n| goals2 = 1\n| years3 = 2012\u20132016\n| clubs3 = [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]]\n| caps3 = 122\n| goals3 = 16\n| years4 = 2017\u20132018\n| clubs4 = [[Tianjin Quanjian F.C.|Tianjin Quanjian]]\n| caps4 = 36\n| goals4 = 5\n| years5 = 2018\u2013\n| clubs5 = [[Borussia Dortmund]]\n| caps5 = 54\n| goals5 = 8\n| nationalyears1 = 2004\n| nationalteam1 = [[Belgium national youth football team|Belgium U15]]\n| nationalcaps1 = 1\n| nationalgoals1 = 0\n| nationalyears2 = 2005\n| nationalteam2 = [[Belgium national youth football team|Belgium U16]]\n| nationalcaps2 = 2\n| nationalgoals2 = 0\n| nationalyears3 = 2005\u20132006\n| nationalteam3 = [[Belgium national under-17 football team|Belgium U17]]\n| nationalcaps3 = 19\n| nationalgoals3 = 0\n| nationalyears4 = 2006\u20132007\n| nationalteam4 = [[Belgium national under-18 football team|Belgium U18]]\n| nationalcaps4 = 5\n| nationalgoals4 = 0\n| nationalyears5 = 2006\n| nationalteam5 = [[Belgium national under-19 football team|Belgium U19]]\n| nationalcaps5 = 3\n| nationalgoals5 = 0\n| nationalyears6 = 2007\u20132009\n| nationalteam6 = [[Belgium national under-21 football team|Belgium U21]]\n| nationalcaps6 = 10\n| nationalgoals6 = 0\n| nationalyears7 = 2008\u2013\n| nationalteam7 = [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]]\n| nationalcaps7 = 105\n| nationalgoals7 = 9\n| medaltemplates = {{Medal|Sport|Men's [[Association football|football]]}}\n{{Medal|Country|{{fb|BEL}}}}\n{{Medal|Comp|[[FIFA World Cup]]}}\n{{Medal|3rd|[[2018 FIFA World Cup|2018 Russia]]|}}\n| club-update = 23:14, 7 March 2020 (UTC)\n| nationalteam-update = 19:36, 16 November 2019 (UTC)\n}}\n'''Axel Laurent Angel Lambert Witsel''' (born 12 January 1989) is a Belgian professional [[association football|footballer]] who plays for German club [[Borussia Dortmund]].<ref name=\"Borussia\">{{cite web|publisher=[[Borussia Dortmund]]|url=https://www.bvb.de/News/Uebersicht/Axel-Witsel-im-BVB-Trainingslager-angekommen|title=Axel Witsel im BVB Trainingslager angekommen|date=6 August 2017|language=German}}</ref> During his play for the [[Belgium national football team|Belgium national team]], he came into the first team as a [[Midfielder#Winger|right-winger]], and can also play [[Midfielder#Attacking midfielder|attacking midfielder]], though his natural position is as a [[Midfielder#Central midfielder|central midfielder]].\n\nHe began his career at hometown club [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]], making 183 appearances and scoring 42 goals while winning five domestic trophies. He was awarded the [[Belgian Golden Shoe]] in 2008. After a season in Portugal with [[S.L. Benfica]], he signed for [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] for a \u20ac40 million fee in 2012. Witsel won four honours during his time in Russia, before leaving for [[Tianjin Quanjian F.C.|Tianjin Quanjian]] in January 2017. He returned to Europe with Borussia Dortmund in August 2018.\n\nWitsel made his senior international debut in 2008 and  earned his 100th [[cap (sport)|cap]] for Belgium on 15 November 2018. He represented the country at the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]], [[UEFA Euro 2016]] and the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]], helping them to third place in the last tournament.\n\n==Club career==\n===Standard Li\u00e8ge===\nOn 17 September 2006, a 17-year-old Witsel made his debut with [[Standard Li\u00e8ge]] during a competitive game against [[FC Brussels]] when he replaced [[Steven Defour]] in the 89th minute. Eleven days later, he made his European debut as a [[substitute (football)|substitute]].{{citation needed|date=January 2017}}\n\nDuring the [[2007\u201308 Belgian First Division|2007\u201308]] season, at 18 years of age, he was a key member in the squad of Standard Li\u00e8ge, winners of the Belgian League title that year. During this year, he formed a very young midfield together with other Belgian talents Defour and [[Marouane Fellaini]]. In the [[2008\u201309 Belgian First Division|following season]], he scored the winning goal [[Penalty kick (association football)|from the penalty spot]] in a [[two-legged match|two-legged playoff]] to decide the championship.{{citation needed|date=January 2017}}\n\nOn 30 August 2009, Witsel sparked controversy when he broke [[Marcin Wasilewski]]'s leg by stamping on his ankle during the match between [[R.S.C. Anderlecht|Anderlecht]] and Standard.<ref>{{cite web|publisher=Sporza |title=Witsel breekt been van Wasilewski in tackle |url=http://www.sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/Jupiler_Pro_League/090830_Wasilewski_tackle_Witsel |accessdate=31 August 2009 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090901061702/http://www.sporza.be/cm/sporza/voetbal/Jupiler_Pro_League/090830_Wasilewski_tackle_Witsel |archivedate=1 September 2009 }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|publisher=YouTube|title=Anderlecht-Standard faute d'Axel Witsel sur Wasilewski |url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=_OapMvlhZOQ|accessdate=31 August 2009}}</ref> Following the tackle, Witsel protested the red card, claiming that it was an accident without intent, before being sent off the pitch. He soon apologised, but was the subject of criticism from several media outlets and numerous [[death threat]]s from angry Anderlecht and [[Poland national football team|Poland]] fans.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://goal.com/en/news/755/europe/2009/09/01/1474358/standard-liege-stars-defour-witsel-receive-death-threats|title=Standard Liege Stars Defour & Witsel Receive Death Threats - Report - Goal.com|date=1 September 2009|publisher=|accessdate=26 June 2016}}</ref> The initial ban until 23 November by the [[Royal Belgian Football Association|Belgian Football Association]],<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.mirror.co.uk/sport/football/news/standard-liege-midfielder-axel-witsel-3372233|title=Standard Liege midfielder Axel Witsel banned for horror tackle|work=MirrorFootball|date=1 September 2009|publisher=|accessdate=26 June 2016}}</ref> was later reduced on appeal to eight matches.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/05092009/58/champions-league-witsel-horror-tackle-ban-reduced.html|title=Yahoo UK & Ireland \u2013 Sports News \u2013 Live Scores \u2013 Results|publisher=|accessdate=26 June 2016}}</ref>\n\n===Benfica===\nWitsel signed for Portuguese club [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] on a five-year deal on 13 July 2011, including a \u20ac40 million buyout clause.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/news/story/_/id/934507/benfica-complete-signing-of-belgium-international-axel-witsel?cc=5901 |title=Benfica sign Witsel |publisher=ESPNFC |date=14 July 2011}}</ref> Witsel scored twice in the 3\u20131 win against [[FC Twente]], in the [[2011\u201312 UEFA Champions League|Champions League play-off second leg]], on 24 August 2011, sending Benfica to the group stages with a 5\u20133 aggregate victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefachampionsleague/season=2012/matches/round=2000262/match=2007565/postmatch/report/index.html |title=Witsel delivers as Benfica oust Twente |publisher=UEFA |date=24 August 2011}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Axel Witsel.jpg|thumb|left|Witsel playing for [[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]] against Zenit in 2012]]\nHe scored the opening goal in a 4\u20131 thrashing of [[Vit\u00f3ria S.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Guimar\u00e3es]] in the [[2011\u201312 Ta\u00e7a da Liga|Ta\u00e7a da Liga]] on 9 January 2012.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lpfp.pt/taca_liga/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20112012&jornada=6&jogo=7308 |title=V.Guimar\u00e3es 1\u20134 Benfica |publisher=LPFP |accessdate=3 December 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120428112211/http://www.lpfp.pt/taca_liga/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20112012&jornada=6&jogo=7308 |archive-date=28 April 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> He then assisted [[Nolito]] in a 4\u20131 league defeat of [[Vit\u00f3ria F.C.|Vit\u00f3ria de Set\u00fabal]]. Witsel scored his fourth goal against [[C.D. Santa Clara|Santa Clara]] on 18 January in a Ta\u00e7a da Liga match.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lpfp.pt/taca_liga/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20112012&jornada=7&jogo=7310 |title=Benfica 2\u20130 Sta. Clara |publisher=LPFP |accessdate=3 December 2012 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130801085810/http://www.lpfp.pt/taca_liga/pages/jogo.aspx?epoca=20112012&jornada=7&jogo=7310 |archive-date=1 August 2013 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref> Benfica reached the final on 14 April against [[Gil Vicente F.C.|Gil Vicente]] and Witsel was awarded the [[Man of the Match]] award as Benfica claimed their fourth Ta\u00e7a da Liga title with a 2\u20131 victory.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lpfp.pt/Pages/WitselfoioManofTheMatch.aspx |title=Witsel foi o Man of The Match |publisher=LPFP |date=15 April 2012 |access-date=3 December 2012 |archive-url=https://archive.is/20120714053927/http://lpfp.pt/Pages/WitselfoioManofTheMatch.aspx |archive-date=14 July 2012 |url-status=dead |df=dmy-all }}</ref>\n\n===Zenit Saint Petersburg===\nOn 3 September 2012, Witsel signed for [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] for \u20ac40 million, after signing a five-year contract.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.fc-zenit.ru/main/news/60736.html|title=\u041e\u0444\u0438\u0446\u0438\u0430\u043b\u044c\u043d\u044b\u0439 \u0441\u0430\u0439\u0442 \u0424\u041a \"\u0417\u0435\u043d\u0438\u0442\"|publisher=|accessdate=26 June 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://web3.cmvm.pt/sdi2004/emitentes/docs/FR41312.pdf |title=Comunicado |language=Portuguese |trans-title=Announcement |date=3 September 2012 |publisher=[[Portuguese Securities Market Commission|CMVM]] |format=PDF |accessdate=31 December 2014}}</ref> Witsel made his debut in the [[2012\u201313 Russian Premier League|Russian Premier League]] on 14 September, replacing [[Konstantin Zyryanov]] in the 70th minute as Zenit fell 2\u20130 to [[FC Terek Grozny|Terek Grozny]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://soccernet.espn.go.com/match?id=342396&cc=5901 |title=Zenit 0 \u2013 2 Terek Grozny |publisher=ESPNFC |date=14 September 2012}}</ref> He scored his first two goals for the club on 30 November when Zenit brushed aside [[FC Spartak Moscow|Spartak Moscow]] 4\u20132 at the [[Luzhniki Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espnfc.com/us/en/gamecast/statistics/id/357869/statistics.html?soccernet=true&cc=5901 |title=Spartak Moscow 2 \u2013 4 Zenit St Petersburg |publisher=ESPNFC |date=30 November 2012}}</ref> Witsel scored Zenit's winner against Terek Grozny on 30 March 2013, an eighth-minute strike, as his side cruised to a 3\u20130 league victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://espnfc.com/us/en/gamecast/statistics/id/358127/statistics.html?soccernet=true&cc=5901 |title=Terek Grozny 0\u20133 Zenit St. Petersburg |publisher=ESPNFC |date=30 March 2013 }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Axel Witsel 2014.jpg|thumb|right|Witsel playing for [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] in 2014]]\nIn Zenit's first match of the [[2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League group stage#Group C|2014\u201315 UEFA Champions League group stage]] on 16 September 2014, Witsel scored Zenit's second goal in a 2\u20130 away victory over former club Benfica.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/news/newsid=2140402.html |title=Familiar Zenit faces come back to haunt Benfica |work=UEFA |date=16 September 2014 |accessdate=17 July 2015 }}</ref> After finishing third in their Champions League group, Zenit were parachuted into the [[2014-15 UEFA Europa League|Europa League]] knockout phase; in the first leg of their Round of 16 clash against [[Torino F.C.|Torino]] on 12 March 2015, Witsel scored on a rebound as Zenit defeated the Italian club 2\u20130.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuropaleague/season=2015/matches/round=2000589/match=2014609/postmatch/report/index.html#zenit+beat+torino |title=Zenit ease to victory over ten-man Torino |work=UEFA |date=12 March 2015 |accessdate=17 July 2015 }}</ref> On 26 April, Witsel scored the game's only goal in the seventeenth minute as Zenit defeated [[FC Arsenal Tula|Arsenal Tula]] in a league match at the [[Petrovsky Stadium]].<ref>{{cite web|url=https://uk.eurosport.yahoo.com/football/russian-premier-league/zenit-st-petersburg-fc-arsenal-tula-18571/ |title=Zenit St Petersburg 1\u20130 FC Arsenal Tula |work=Yahoo Sports! |date=26 April 2015 |accessdate=17 July 2015 }}</ref> On Sunday 17 May, Witsel played the full 90 minutes as Zenit drew 1\u20131 with [[FC Ufa]], earning the point they needed to secure the [[2014\u201315 Russian Premier League|Premier League]] crown, the club's fourth overall and Witsel's first with Zenit.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.dailymail.co.uk/sport/football/article-3085421/Andre-Villas-Boas-leads-Zenit-St-Petersburg-Russian-Premier-League-title-ill-fated-spells-Chelsea-Tottenham.html |title=Andre Villas-Boas leads Zenit St Petersburg to Russian Premier League title after ill-fated spells at Chelsea and Tottenham |work=Daily Mail |date=17 May 2015 |accessdate=17 July 2015 }}</ref>\n\n[[File:Dundolk-Zenit (21).jpg|thumb|left|Witsel playing for [[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]] against Dundalk in 2016]]\nIn the [[2015 Russian Super Cup]] on 12 July 2015, Witsel converted his penalty shot in a 4\u20132 penalty shoot-out victory over [[FC Lokomotiv Moscow]] after the match had finished 1\u20131.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.rfpl.org/match/match_10880.html |title=\u0421\u0443\u043f\u0435\u0440\u043a\u0443\u0431\u043e\u043a \u0420\u043e\u0441\u0441\u0438\u0438 \u043f\u043e \u0444\u0443\u0442\u0431\u043e\u043b\u0443 2015, \u0424\u0438\u043d\u0430\u043b |work=RFPL |date=12 July 2015 |accessdate=17 July 2015 |language=Russian }}</ref>\n\n===Tianjin Quanjian===\nOn 3 January 2017, Zenit officially announced that Witsel has moved to Chinese club [[Tianjin Quanjian F.C.|Tianjin Quanjian]].<ref name=\"toChina\">{{cite web|publisher=[[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg]]|url=http://fc-zenit.ru/news/feed/2017/01/03/aksel-vitsel-prodolzhit-kareru-v-kitae/|title=Witsel will continue his career in China|date=3 January 2017|language=Russian}}</ref>\n\nOn 4 March 2017, Witsel made his debut for Quanjian in a 2\u20130 loss to [[Guangzhou R&F F.C.|Guangzhou R&F]].<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.espnfc.com.au/chinese-super-league/story/3074387/alexandre-pato-struggles-as-tianjin-quanjian-slump-vs-guangzhou-randf|title=Alexandre Pato struggles as Tianjin Quanjian slump vs. Guangzhou R&F|date=4 March 2017|work=ESPN}}</ref> A week later he scored the club's first ever goal in the [[Chinese Super League]] during a 1\u20131 draw with [[Shanghai Greenland Shenhua F.C.|Shanghai Greenland Shenhua]].<ref>{{cite news|url=https://www.msn.com/en-my/video/news/witsel-scores-quanjians-maiden-csl-goal/vp-AAo96zl|title=Witsel scores Quanjian's maiden CSL goal|date=11 March 2017|work=MSN}}</ref>\n\n===Borussia Dortmund===\nOn 6 August 2018, Witsel signed for [[Bundesliga]] club [[Borussia Dortmund]] and agreed a four-year contract which lasts until 30 June 2022.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.skysports.com/football/news/11899/11463405/axel-witsel-to-join-borussia-dortmund-from-tianjin-quanjian|title=Axel Witsel to join Borussia Dortmund from Tianjin Quanjian|publisher=SkySports|accessdate=7 August 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bvb.de/eng/News/Overview/Axel-Witsel-arrives-at-the-BVB-training-camp|title=Axel Witsel arrives at the BVB training camp |publisher= Borussia Dortmund|accessdate=7 August 2018}}</ref> On 21 August, he scored an equalizing goal in the [[Association football#Duration and tie-breaking methods|stoppage time]] to make it 1\u20131 after coming on as a substitute on his debut for the club against [[SpVgg Greuther F\u00fcrth]] in the [[2018\u201319 DFB-Pokal|DFB-Pokal]] first round match and later his side went on to win the match in the [[Overtime (sports)|extra time]] with a 2-1 victory.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bbc.com/sport/football/45254350|title=Axel Witsel saves Borussia Dortmund on debut in German Cup|publisher=BBC Sport|accessdate=21 August 2018}}</ref> Witsel scored his first Bundesliga goal on his league debut for the club with an overhead kick in a 4\u20131 victory over [[RB Leipzig]] on 26 August.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.bundesliga.com/en/news/Bundesliga/borussia-dortmung-rb-leipzig-live-blog-pulisic-reus-witsel-werner-delaney-511044.jsp|title=Borussia Dortmund 4-1 RB Leipzig: As it happened!|publisher=Bundesliga|accessdate=27 August 2018}}</ref>\n\n==International career==\nPrior to making his international debut for the senior side, he played for the [[Belgium national under-21 football team|under-21 side]] in 2007 earning nine caps as well as helping his side reach the semi-finals of the [[2007 UEFA European Under-21 Football Championship]].\n\nOn 26 March 2008, Witsel made his international debut during a friendly game against [[Morocco national football team|Morocco]]. The match resulted in a 1\u20134 loss, but Witsel scored his first goal for [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]].<ref name = \"First int'l goal\">{{cite news |title=Axel Witsel marque, Stijn Stijnen se troue deux fois |url=http://archives.lesoir.be/-p-axel-witsel-marque-stijn-stijnen-se-troue-deux-fois-_t-20080327-00FFGG.html |work=Le Soir |date=27 March 2008 |accessdate=4 December 2014 |language=French}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Axel Witsel Belgium.jpg|thumb|left|Witsel lining up for [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] before playing [[Austria national football team|Austria]] in the qualification for [[UEFA Euro 2012]]]]\nWitsel's first goal in an competitive international match came a day short of three years after the Morocco goal, in the sixth minute against [[Austria national football team|Austria]] in [[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying Group A|Group A]] of the [[UEFA Euro 2012 qualifying]] process, and his second would come in the second half.<ref name=\"Goals vs Austria\" /> However, Belgian hopes of qualifying for [[UEFA Euro 2012]] were dashed on 11 October 2011, by defeat to [[Germany national football team|Germany]] coupled with [[Turkey national football team|Turkey]]'s victory over [[Azerbaijan national football team|Azerbaijan]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Germany stamp out Belgium's fire|date=11 October 2011|first=Steffen|last=Potter|work=uefa.com|publisher=Union of European Football Associations|accessdate=24 January 2018|url=http://www.uefa.com/uefaeuro/season=2012/matches/round=15171/match=2002112/postmatch/report/index.html#germany+oust+belgium}}</ref>\n\nOn 13 May 2014, Witsel was named in [[2014 FIFA World Cup squads#Belgium|Belgium's squad]] for the [[2014 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite news|title=Adnan Januzaj included in Belgium's World Cup squad|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/27395150|accessdate=15 May 2014|newspaper=[[BBC Sport]]|date=13 May 2014}}</ref> He started in midfield in the team's first game of the tournament, a 2\u20131 win against [[Algeria national football team|Algeria]] in [[Belo Horizonte]].<ref>{{cite news|last1=Chowdhury|first1=Saj|title=Belgium 2\u20131 Algeria|url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/0/football/25285127|accessdate=17 June 2014|work=[[BBC Sport]]|date=17 June 2014}}</ref>\n\nWitsel also featured in the [[UEFA Euro 2016 squads#Belgium|Belgian squad]] at [[UEFA Euro 2016]], announced on 31 May 2016.<ref>{{Cite tweet |author=BelgianRedDevils |user=@BelRedDevils |number=737693491627720705 |date=31 May 2016 |title=.OFFICIAL ! Our final #Euro2016 squad list & numbers ! #TousenFrance |access-date=24 January 2018}}</ref> He scored his first tournament goal during the Championships, in a [[UEFA Euro 2016 Group E|Group E]] match against the [[Republic of Ireland national football team|Republic of Ireland]].<ref name = \"Euro 2016 goal\">{{cite news |first=Sid |last=Lowe |title=Belgium get going as Romelu Lukaku punishes Republic of Ireland |url=https://www.theguardian.com/football/2016/jun/18/belgium-republic-of-ireland-euro-2016-match-report |website=The Guardian |date=18 June 2016 |accessdate=14 October 2016}}</ref>\n\n[[File:Axel Witsel 2018.jpg|thumb|right|Axel Witsel playing for [[Belgium national football team|Belgium]] during the [[2018 FIFA World Cup]]]]\nHe scored twice in [[2018 FIFA World Cup qualification (UEFA)|2018 FIFA World Cup qualification]], both in wide victories over [[Gibraltar national football team|Gibraltar]].<ref>{{cite news |last1=Dorman |first1=Matt |title=Belgium 9 Gibraltar 0: Trebles for Meunier and Lukaku as Hazard makes scoring return |url=http://www.goal.com/en-us/news/55/main/2017/08/31/38240092/belgium-9-gibraltar-0-trebles-for-meunier-and-lukaku-as |accessdate=4 September 2018 |publisher=Goal.com |date=31 August 2017}}</ref> Manager [[Roberto Mart\u00ednez]] named him in the squad for the [[2018 FIFA World Cup|final tournament]] in Russia.<ref>{{cite news |title=World Cup 2018: Belgium include Vincent Kompany but Christian Benteke misses out |url=https://www.bbc.co.uk/sport/football/44353673 |accessdate=4 September 2018 |publisher=BBC Sport |date=4 June 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nIn June 2015, Witsel married his longtime [[Romania]]n girlfriend, Rafaella, with whom he has two children.<ref>{{cite news|last1=|first1=|title=Axel Witsel en tr\u00e8s charmante compagnie|url=http://www.dhnet.be/archive/axel-witsel-en-tres-charmante-compagnie-51b7e153e4b0de6db992d370|5=|language=French|accessdate=23 April 2014|work=[[La Derni\u00e8re Heure]]|date=23 October 2012|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20170831220526/http://www.dhnet.be/archive/axel-witsel-en-tres-charmante-compagnie-51b7e153e4b0de6db992d370|archive-date=31 August 2017|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.sudinfo.be/1310603/article/2015-06-14/axel-rafaella-witsel-eblouissants-lors-de-leur-mariage-religieux-photos|language=French|title=Axel & Rafaella Witsel \u00e9blouissants lors de leur mariage religieux|date=13 June 2015|work=Sudinfo.be|access-date=31 August 2017|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160625022110/http://www.sudinfo.be/1310603/article/2015-06-14/axel-rafaella-witsel-eblouissants-lors-de-leur-mariage-religieux-photos|archive-date=25 June 2016|url-status=dead|df=dmy-all}}</ref>\nHe is of [[Martinique|Martiniquais]] descent through his father.<ref>{{cite news |title=Mondial 2018 - France Belgique: Axel Witsel, l'autre Antillais endiabl\u00e9 |url=https://la1ere.francetvinfo.fr/mondial-2018-france-belgique-axel-witsel-autre-martiniquais-endiable-607799.html |accessdate=11 July 2018 |agency=franceinfo |publisher=franceinfo |date=10 July 2018}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |last1=Dalmat |first1=Syanie |title=Axel Witsel, le Belge qui aurait pu jouer pour la France |url=https://www.lequipe.fr/Football/Article/Axel-witsel-un-martiniquais-chez-les-belges/920984 |accessdate=11 July 2018 |publisher=L'Equipe |date=10 July 2018}}</ref>\n\n==Career statistics==\n===Club===\n[[File:Dundolk-Zenit (9).jpg|thumb|upright|Witsel in [[UEFA Europa League]] action for Zenit, facing [[Dundalk F.C.|Dundalk]] in 2016]]\n\n{{updated|match played 11 March 2020}}<ref name=\"honours\" />\n\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"text-align: center\"\n|-\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Club\n!rowspan=\"2\"|Season\n!colspan=\"3\"|League\n!colspan=\"2\"|Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|League Cup\n!colspan=\"2\"|Continental\n!colspan=\"2\"|Other\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n|-\n!Division!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals!!Apps!!Goals\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[Standard Li\u00e8ge]]\n|[[2006\u201307 Standard Li\u00e8ge season|2006\u201307]]\n|rowspan=\"5\"|[[Belgian Pro League]]\n|16||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||1||0||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||17||2\n|-\n|[[2007\u201308 Standard Li\u00e8ge season|2007\u201308]]\n|33||7||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||3||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||36||8\n|-\n|[[2008\u201309 Standard Li\u00e8ge season|2008\u201309]]\n|35||8||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||10||1||1||0||46||9\n|-\n|[[2009\u201310 Standard Li\u00e8ge season|2009\u201310]]\n|27||6||1||1||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||12||3||1||1||41||11\n|-\n|[[2010\u201311 Standard Li\u00e8ge season|2010\u201311]]\n|37||10||6||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||43||12\n|-\n!colspan=\"2\"|Total\n!148!!33!!7!!3!!0!!0!!26!!5!!2!!1!!183!!42\n|-\n|rowspan=3|[[S.L. Benfica|Benfica]]\n|[[2011\u201312 S.L. Benfica season|2011\u201312]]\n|rowspan=2|[[Primeira Liga]]\n|29||1||1||0||4||2||14||2||colspan=\"2\"|\u2014||49||5\n|-\n|[[2012\u201313 S.L. Benfica season|2012\u201313]]\n|3||0||0||0||0||0||colspan=2|\u2014||colspan=2|\u2014||3||0\n|-\n!colspan=2|Total\n!32!!1!!1!!0!!4!!2!!14!!2!!0!!0!!52!!5\n|-\n|rowspan=\"6\"|[[FC Zenit Saint Petersburg|Zenit Saint Petersburg]]\n